 sumed, or it can add/give to surface water worsening by moving sideways into streams, lakes or bays. 
 Direct runoff from fields also adds/gives to surface 
 water worsening. Excess (vitamins, minerals, protein, etc.) (nitrogen and 
 phosphorus) in surface waters cause (sudden, huge growths of seaweed, etc.) 
 and eutrophication, which can lead to problems with 
 odors, fish kills, and other (worries about the health of the Earth). 
 Control of nitrogen as an farming-based input has 
 been talked to/looked at for both commercial (material that makes plants grow better) and animal sources (Trachtenberg and Ogg, 1994). Methods 
 of control that have been talked about include input reduction, improved crop-watering/rinsing with water management, and cover 
 
